<task id="025" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Always-on Tools — Register SearchDocuments, QueryDataverse, GetCurrentEntityContext on every session</title>
    <phase>Phase 2: Tool Registry + Discovery</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>020</dependencies>
    <blocks>052</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF code wire-up affecting every Assistant chat session; ADR-008/ADR-010/ADR-015 binding; tags include bff-api + ai</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Distinct scope from Group C (meta-tools — different files under `MetaTools/`). Touches `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/AlwaysOnTools/` + a Chat session registration site in `SprkChatAgent` or kernel-builder extension. May touch `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` if a chat-session bootstrap line is added — coordinate with task 021 which also touches that file (different line ranges).</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Register the three always-on foundational Tools — `SearchDocuments`, `QueryDataverse`, `GetCurrentEntityContext` — with every Assistant session, alongside the three meta-tools (`FindResources`, `GetResourceDetail`, `InvokeResource` from tasks 022/023/024). These three are high-frequency primitives that should be directly callable by the LLM without the `FindResources` discovery hop. Wire them to existing BFF services (no new logic — these wrap existing capabilities as `[KernelFunction]`-decorated facades).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET 8 / Semantic Kernel engineer familiar with the `SprkChatAgent` / kernel-builder bootstrap pattern, existing BFF services for document search (SPE / AI Search), Dataverse query, and surface-context resolution.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three concrete outcomes:
    1. **Three thin always-on Tool implementations** — `SearchDocumentsTool`, `QueryDataverseTool`, `GetCurrentEntityContextTool` — each a `[KernelFunction]`-decorated facade over an existing service (no new business logic; wrap and forward).
    2. **Per-session registration wire-up** — `AddActionEngineModule()` extension registers these three Tools (plus the three meta-tools from 022/023/024) into the SK kernel bootstrap for every chat session. Default playbook seed (task 052) references these by name.
    3. **Context-aware promotion plumbing** — leverage `IsAlwaysOnInAssistant` + `PromoteInContexts` flags from the data model (task 020). These three are universally always-on; the registration code also reads `PromoteInContexts` from Tool Registry to promote Tools per surface context (e.g., matter-specific Tools on Matter form). The promotion logic lives here; the universally always-on three are the seed.

    Deliverable: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/AlwaysOnTools/` folder with three Tool files + session-registration wire-up + tests.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Design.md §4.5 + §7.4.2 documents the always-on Tool pattern: "high-frequency Tools as always-on — skip the FindResources hop." The three foundational Tools (`SearchDocuments`, `QueryDataverse`, `GetCurrentEntityContext`) are universally always-on per design.md §7.4.3 system prompt directive: "Use your tools (`SearchDocuments`, `QueryDataverse`, `FindResources`) to look up the answer; cite the source in your response."

      Existing services to wrap:
      - **SearchDocuments**: wraps SPE / AI Search document query. Existing service: check `Services/Ai/` for an AI Search abstraction or use `Azure.Search.Documents` directly against the documents index.
      - **QueryDataverse**: wraps Dataverse client query (parameterized fetch). Existing service: `IDataverseClient` already DI-registered.
      - **GetCurrentEntityContext**: reads `surfaceContext` from the chat session (entity type + id from `sprk_aichatcontextmap` resolution). Existing service: `ISurfaceContextResolver` or equivalent — established by Phase 5 SpaarkeAi launcher work; for Phase 2 this task may need to introduce a minimal `ISurfaceContextProvider` interface that Phase 5 fills in.

      Per-session registration:
      - SK kernel is built per-session in `SprkChatAgent` (or a kernel-factory). This task adds a Tool-registration step in that bootstrap.
      - The data model from task 020 (`ToolRegistryEntry.IsAlwaysOnInAssistant` flag) drives a registry query: at session start, query Tool Registry for `IsAlwaysOnInAssistant = true` AND (`PromoteInContexts` empty OR contains current surface context). Register all matching Tools.
      - The three universal Tools are seeded with `IsAlwaysOnInAssistant = true` + `PromoteInContexts = []` (universal).

      EndpointMappingExtensions.cs may need a line added if a new chat-session bootstrap endpoint is exposed; otherwise this task only touches the kernel builder + AddActionEngineModule.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/AlwaysOnTools/SearchDocumentsTool.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/AlwaysOnTools/QueryDataverseTool.cs</file>
