  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API + BackgroundService. Tools run in-proc.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter auth at the chat endpoint. Tool-level permission checks happen at dispatch (task 026) — these always-on facades MUST NOT re-implement auth; they delegate.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism. `AlwaysOnToolRegistrar` registered once via `AddActionEngineModule()`. Existing services (Dataverse client, AI Search client, surface context resolver) injected — no new singletons.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">PublicContracts boundary. These three Tools are internal SK facades — NOT exposed via the PublicContracts facade. CRUD-side callers reach equivalent capability via existing Dataverse/SPE clients, not these wrappers.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Audit Tier 2 + Tier 3 applies via dispatch path (task 026) when the LLM calls these Tools. No manual audit calls needed in the facades themselves.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Errors from the wrapped service surface as `KernelFunctionResult` with error; LLM sees the structured error and can adapt.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">No new NuGet packages. Wrap existing services.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge: placement justification (in BFF — latency-critical chat-agent registration). Zero publish-size delta.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Design.md §7.4.2: high-frequency Tools as always-on. `IsAlwaysOnInAssistant` flag + `PromoteInContexts` filter drive context-aware promotion at session start.</constraint>
  </constraints>

