  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm baseline build passes; task 020 merged or branch-loadable; `SprkChatAgent.cs` kernel bootstrap site identified (line range where existing tools are registered).</step>
    <step order="1">Read all files in `&lt;knowledge&gt;&lt;files&gt;`. Pay attention to design.md §4.5 + §7.4.2 + §7.4.3 (the always-on Tool registration model and system prompt directive).</step>
    <step order="2">Identify the underlying services to wrap:
      - SearchDocuments → existing AI Search client or SPE search service. If absent, escalate (DO NOT introduce new search infrastructure).
      - QueryDataverse → existing `IDataverseClient` or equivalent. Confirm it supports parameterized fetch with entity-type + filter.
      - GetCurrentEntityContext → `ISurfaceContextProvider` interface. If absent, introduce a minimal stub here that returns `null` (Phase 5 fills in the actual implementation via `ChatLaunchContext`).</step>
    <step order="3">Implement `SearchDocumentsTool.cs`: `[KernelFunction, Description("Search Spaarke document storage for documents matching the query. Returns top results with citations.")]` `Task&lt;SearchResult[]&gt; SearchDocumentsAsync(string query, int topK = 5)`. Inject the search service; forward + map results.</step>
    <step order="4">Implement `QueryDataverseTool.cs`: `[KernelFunction, Description("Query Dataverse for records of a specified entity type matching a filter. Returns lightweight record summaries with citation IDs.")]` `Task&lt;DataverseQueryResult[]&gt; QueryDataverseAsync(string entityType, string filter)`. Inject Dataverse client; respect caller's data-access scope.</step>
    <step order="5">Implement `GetCurrentEntityContextTool.cs`: `[KernelFunction, Description("Return the current entity context (entity type + id) for this Assistant session — e.g., the matter the user opened the chat from.")]` `Task&lt;EntityContext?&gt; GetCurrentEntityContextAsync()`. Returns null when no surface context (e.g., SpaarkeAi landing).</step>
    <step order="6">Implement `AlwaysOnToolRegistrar.cs`: at session start, queries Tool Registry for `IsAlwaysOnInAssistant = true` AND (`PromoteInContexts` empty OR includes current surface context). Registers matching Tools (including the three universal facades) into the kernel for the session. Place in `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/AlwaysOnTools/`. Expose `RegisterAlwaysOnToolsAsync(Kernel kernel, ISurfaceContext context)`.</step>
    <step order="7">Wire `AlwaysOnToolRegistrar` into the kernel bootstrap. Locate the existing tool-registration call site in `SprkChatAgent.cs` (or kernel-builder factory). Add `await registrar.RegisterAlwaysOnToolsAsync(kernel, currentContext);` adjacent to existing registrations. Verify ordering: meta-tools (022/023/024) + always-on tools (this task) all registered before the first LLM call.</step>
    <step order="8">Register `AlwaysOnToolRegistrar` + each Tool in `AddActionEngineModule()`. Stay under the ≤15 non-framework registration count (ADR-010). If close to budget, consolidate Tools behind a single registrar.</step>
    <step order="9">Write unit tests at `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/AlwaysOnTools/`: (a) `SearchDocumentsTool` forwards correctly to underlying service, (b) `QueryDataverseTool` respects entity-type filter, (c) `GetCurrentEntityContextTool` returns null when no context + populated when context present, (d) `AlwaysOnToolRegistrar` registers expected Tools given a mocked Tool Registry response, (e) registrar respects `PromoteInContexts` filter (entity-specific Tools only register when surface matches).</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` on the new files; `adr-check` verifies ADR-008 (no in-facade auth re-implementation), ADR-010 (DI count under budget — verify with grep on `Services.Add*` in `AddActionEngineModule`), ADR-013 (NOT exposed via PublicContracts), ADR-029 (no new packages). Build + tests pass.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 025 ✅. Update `current-task.md`. Note dependency on Phase 5 for actual `ISurfaceContextProvider` implementation (stub in this task).</step>
    <step order="11">Document the DI count budget status (current vs ADR-010 limit) and any deviations in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/`. Commit with brief recap.</step>
  </steps>

