  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All three always-on Tools (`SearchDocumentsTool`, `QueryDataverseTool`, `GetCurrentEntityContextTool`) exist with `[KernelFunction]` decoration and forward to existing services without re-implementing business logic.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`AlwaysOnToolRegistrar.RegisterAlwaysOnToolsAsync` queries the Tool Registry for `IsAlwaysOnInAssistant = true` Tools and registers them into the per-session kernel — verified by unit test.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`PromoteInContexts` filter applied: entity-specific Tools register only when surface context matches — verified by unit test.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Wire-up in `SprkChatAgent` kernel bootstrap: every chat session has the three universal Tools + the three meta-tools (from 022/023/024) registered before the first LLM call — verified by integration smoke test (start session → list registered kernel functions).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">DI registration stays under ADR-010 ≤15 non-framework count — verified by grep + manual count in `AddActionEngineModule`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">NOT exposed via `PublicContracts/IActionEngineFacade.cs` (ADR-013) — verified by grep.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new NuGet packages added (NFR-10 preserved). All Tools wrap existing services.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Supports spec gates G2 (conversational invocation) + G7 (hallucination guardrails — system prompt §7.4.3 directs LLM to use these always-on Tools to ground responses).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The `ISurfaceContextProvider` interface introduced here is Phase 5's collaborator. Phase 5 task 050 (SpaarkeAi `ChatLaunchContext` parsing) fills in the actual implementation. The Phase 2 stub returns null context — chat sessions launched without surface context (e.g., SpaarkeAi landing) work correctly even before Phase 5.

    DI budget watch (ADR-010 ≤15 non-framework registrations): this task adds up to 5 (three Tools + registrar + surface context provider stub). Consolidate Tools behind the registrar if needed — register only the registrar in DI, then have the registrar build the Tools internally.

    The system prompt §7.4.3 directive references these Tools by name. If a Tool name changes here, update `design.md §7.4.3` to keep the prompt directive accurate, and ensure the default playbook seed (task 052) references the correct names.

    EndpointMappingExtensions.cs note: this task may NOT need to touch that file if the existing chat endpoint already handles session bootstrap inside `SprkChatAgent`. Verify before assuming a registration line is needed.
  </notes>

